args: The sun rises on another day...\nI only have seven more until my\nnext dance performance.
I need to start training rigorously for it.
No! No more rigorous training!\nYou mustn't overexert yourself\nany longer!
Forcing yourself to endure things that\nhurt you will wreak havoc on your\nmental health. But if you still insist...
Is that not a tad, er...drastic? I have\nno desire to do battle with you.
Oh! P-pardon. I don't know what came\nover me.
Regardless, if you want to get better,\nbelieve in me and rest. Listen to your\nheart.
My heart? Hurk...\nAnd yet, my stomach...!
I-I need to go to the latrine!\nPlease, it's an emergency!
So your heart speaks through your\nstomach? Well... Whatever helps\nyou take care of yourself.
They spent several days together\nas nurse and patient.
No, Hanabusa! You must not train!
But I must use my free time somehow!
Then let's do something more fun.\nHmm... Well, I can't think of anything\nmore fun than a medical check-up!
So, how are you feeling? Does it hurt\nwhen I put pressure here? Or here?
Um... I feel like this is barely any\ndifferent from how we usually are.
I thought I told you that you're not\nallowed to train!
But not practicing at all is starting to\nmake me feel anxious. Please, I need to—
Get back here, you little punk!\nI said NO TRAINING!
Oh, you've done it now. You're not the\nonly one who goes buckwild when they're\nangry!
I'm not gonna roll over and take your\nabuse! Now I'M mad, too! Hurgleblurgle!
Stop shouting nonsense, you stupid RUNT!
I said ENOUGH with the alphabet soup!\nSKREEEEEEE!
*pant* *pant* I feel a lot better after that.
*pant* I'm glad to hear that. Shouting\nseems to help you relieve stress.
We'll have to play Furious Freaks again\nsometime.
I feel like my eyes have been opened to\na new kind of dance—a new world of\nemotional interaction.
Eventually, the night before the\ndance performance arrived...
What are you doing out here?
I was looking at the moon.
It certainly is beautiful. Does looking\nat it help to calm you?
Yes. I feel as serene as the night air.\nIt's almost an out-of-body sensation.
You've worked very hard in coming this\nfar. I imagine those stomach pains will\nno longer trouble you.
Congratulations, Hanabusa.\nYou've returned to your true self.
Hm? Didn't you once aspire to be like\nthe moon?
I certainly did. But not quite in that sense.
I wanted to shine brightly like it instead.
So it...wasn't about being calm, then?

No. I wanted to be a dancer who would
illuminate and guide people. Who would
be revered and looked up to—just like
the moon.
I was desperate to reach that goal,\nbut in the end, I... I...
I lost myself, I left my country...\nWhat is even left for me now?
My goal is unfulfilled, and the moon\nseems further away than ever.
Thus dawned the day of the performance. Together,\nAeleen and Hanabusa made their way to the venue.
What's wrong?! Are you all right?
But why? You seemed to be on the mend!
You mustn't! We should call off the\nperformance instead.
Your scars are deeper than I thought.\nYou're going to need more rehabilitation.
Whatever you try, it's not\ngoing to work on him.
How can you be so sure?
You tried yourself, didn't you? You nursed\nhim to health with everything you had.
If YOUR efforts were in vain, then how\ncould anyone else expect to do better?
Well... Not quite. I know exactly why\nnobody has been able to heal him.
He doesn't WANT to be healed.
